{"key":"post-10473544","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10473544</id>\n<content>The best scale I've found for measuring light is the Kelvin scale.&amp;nbsp; In short, it refers to the color of light that a &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_body&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;black body radiator&lt;/a&gt; would emit if heated to a certain temperature Celsius.&amp;nbsp; Mushrooms pin and grow best with light in the 5,000K to 7,000K range, thus 7,000 Kelvin is the color you'd see if the metal was heated to 7,000 degrees Celsius.&amp;nbsp; The scale is actually counter-intuitive since the hotter you heat the black body, the 'cooler' the color temperature.&amp;nbsp;  There's more info about lighting at the bottom of the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;terrarium tek&lt;/a&gt; page on my website.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10473756</next>\n<prev>10473454</prev>\n<first>10473406</first>\n<last>10475959</last>\n<when>1244514898</when>\n<utime>06/09/09 05:34 AM</utime>\n</post>"}